Signal Tower at Red Crown
[trigger settlement]

The construction crew is dead. Six bodies arranged in a half-circle facing the unfinished signal tower, hands bound behind their backs, throats cut. A civil priest stands among them with a bloodied knife, wrapping each corpse's tools in their work-cloth like funeral offerings. His robes are clean except for the sleeves. When he sees you approach, he doesn't startle or hide the blade.

"The Lattice is a corruption," he says, voice steady and rehearsed. "Every tower extends its reach. Every rail spike pins the land to an artificial pattern." He gestures at the bodies with something like tenderness. "They were given the choice to cease their work. They chose the wages instead."

The wind shifts and you catch the smell. Fresh enough that he's been here less than an hour. The nearest Kesharat patrol depot is half a day's ride east. The nearest clan settlement nearly as far west. His water skin sits beside a bedroll and cookpot. He's been camping at the tower site, watching the construction, waiting.

He notices your ring. The merchant's signet catches the light. "You carry the mark of those who feed the machine," he says. "But you walk alone. That suggests doubt." He plants the knife in the sand between you, within reach of either.

